<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id6c0f83db-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s1483"><num value="1483">§ 1483.</num><heading> Foreign government ships; immunity</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">No measures may be taken under authority of this chapter against any warship or other ship owned or operated by a country and used, for the time being, only on Government noncommercial service.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id6c0f83dc-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">(<ref href="/us/pl/93/248/s14">Pub. L. 93–248, § 14</ref>, <date date="1974-02-05">Feb. 5, 1974</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/88/10">88 Stat. 10</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
